How do I use the `getlastimportfrom` command to retrieve the last import from all systems on the chain?

The `getlastimportfrom` command doesn't retrieve the last import from all systems on the chain. Instead, it returns the last import from a specific originating system, identified by its "systemname" argument. To use this command, you need to specify the name or ID of the system you're interested in.
What is the default value of the "systemname" argument in the `getlastimportfrom` command?

The "systemname" argument in the `getlastimportfrom` command is not optional with a default value. It is an optional argument, but if you don't provide it, the command won't work. You need to specify the name or ID of the system you want to retrieve the last import from.
Can I use the `getlastimportfrom` command to retrieve the last import from a system that is not on the current chain?
No, the `getlastimportfrom` command only returns the last import from a specific system on the current chain. It doesn't have the ability to retrieve information from systems on other chains.
